    "name": "James Brown",
    "profile": "American singer, songwriter, and musician.\r\n\r\nBorn: 3 May 1933 near Barnwell, South Carolina, USA.\r\nPassed Away: 25 December 2006 in Atlanta, Georgia, USA (aged 73).\r\n\r\nJames Brown was raised in poverty in Augusta, Georgia.\r\n\r\nPreviously worked as a shoe shiner, car washer & a cotton picker.\r\n\r\n1950s: Joined the Gospel Starlighters in 1953, a vocal quartet led by [a=Bobby Byrd], after completing a four-year stint in prison for robbery. As Brown became the focal point of the act, the group changed its name to 'The Famous Flames' and its focus from gospel to R&B. In 1955 The Famous Flames record \"Please Please Please\" at the studio of WIBB in Macon, Georgia. In 1958 James Brown's first #1 hit, \"Try Me\", is released. It was the best-selling R&B single of 1958, and the first of 17 chart-topping R&B singles by Brown over the next two decades.\r\n\r\n1965: Records \"Papa's Got a Brand New Bag\", a revolutionary single that ushers in a whole new era of soul music. Released that summer, it tops the ",
